{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1444307144,"nonce":"Nv61hnYQuZNe8mmqDEa2phQBZdA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0NjUyMTk0NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/304#issuecomment-146521945"},"message":"I did not test this because by that time cairo didn't work either, but I guess cairo is neccesairy to solve:\nhttps://biostar.usegalaxy.org/p/9170/  So I would prefer cairo as part of R.\n\nAt the link http://sourceforge.net/p/mingw-w64/bugs/396/ they claim to solve 1.12.14 with a diff file:\n\n```\n--- mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14.orig/build/configure.ac.warnings\n+++ mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14/build/configure.ac.warnings\n@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ dnl options. Namely, the following:\ndnl -flto working really needs a test link, not just a compile\nsafe_MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN\"\n-MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto\"\n+MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto -ffat-lto-objects -fuse-linker-plugin\"\nAC_TRY_LINK([],\nint main(int argc, char **argv) { return 0; }\n,[],[\n--- mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14.orig/configure\n+++ mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14/configure\n@@ -18162,7 +18162,7 @@ MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -erroff=E_ENUM_T\nsafe_MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN\"\n-MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto\"\n+MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto -ffat-lto-objects -fuse-linker-plugin\"\ncat confdefs.h - \u003c\u003c_ACEOF \u003econftest.$ac_ext\n/ end confdefs.h. /\n```\n\nBecause you can't include a patch file within a package definition (allows only 1 file), you could hack the tool_dependencies such that it creates the diff and patches the package, but this is kind of upgrading the package locally. But if you solve it this way, package_cairo_1_12_14 doesn't need to be deprecated.\n\n\u003e Perhaps we change the already released R version to use cairo-1.14.2, and to release newer version of R without cairo?\n\nI would go for solving R 3.2.1 as well, since we don't know how many non iuc/dev-team tools depend on it. If we solve it within R 3.2.1, only a re-up to the TS is neccessairy.","files":null}]}